<item>
            <title>[LU-11664] LNet Router: push updates when router interfaces change</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11664</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A router can bring up/down its interfaces if it hasn&apos;t received any messages on that interface for a configurable period (alive_router_ping_timeout). When this even occures the router can now push its status change to the peers it&apos;s talking to in order to inform them of the change in its status. This will allow the router users to handle asym router failures quicker.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
